20. We reiterated our audit recommendations that Management to (a) require all concerned accountable officers to immediately settle their cash advances in accordance with the pertinent sections of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;
21. (b) direct the Municipal Accountant to monitor and strictly enforce the liquidation of cash advances within the prescribed period, and see to it that no additional cash advance shall be allowed unless the previous ones are settled or properly accounted for; and
22. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to conduct regular evaluation/validation of all outstanding accounts; send demand letters to officers and employees with long outstanding accounts, and impose sanctions when necessary, such as withholding of their salaries as provided in the Circular; and if warranted, request for the write-off of long-overdue cash advances in accordance with the procedures under COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We recommended that Management:
a) Stop the practice of recording purchases of supplies and materials directly to the related expense account and, henceforth, record purchases and utilization of these items in accordance with Sections 114 and 121 of the Manual on NGAS for LGUs, Volume I;
b) Require the requisitioning office needing the supplies and materials to prepare and submit the RIS to the Municipal Treasurer as the property custodian on a weekly basis;
c) Require the Municipal Treasurer/Property Custodian to consolidate all the RIS on the SSMI and submit the same to the Accounting Office; and
d) Require the Municipal Accountant to record to the related expense accounts the supplies consumed based on the SSMI and to maintain perpetual inventory records to be reconciled periodically with the records of the Municipal Treasurer in order to fairly present the expense and inventory accounts in the financial statements.
